szBRDesc: US SOCOM issued a solicitation for the procurement of SOF Combat Assault Rifles (SCAR) in 2003, and this is what FN came up with. Widely customizable and extremely durable; if ever a gun had promise, the SCAR does.

szItemDesc: FN's latest addition to the SCAR family is the "L" or Light version, chambered in 5.56mm NATO. The CQC version is for MOUT or dense terrain.
szBRDesc: The FN SCAR was designed to be more customizable than any other weapon, period. Experts agree: it's nearly perfect. This version is chambered for the lighter 5.56mm NATO round.

szItemDesc: A red headed bastard step child of the Eastern AK-47 and the Western M-16, this Belgian beauty has an integral flash suppressor.
szBRDesc: A red headed bastard step child of the Eastern AK-47 and the Western M-16, this Belgian beauty has an integral flash suppressor and a Swedish twin. In the words of Gershwin, who could ask for anything more... besides a lighter trigger pull.

szItemDesc: This ambitious sniper rifle fires 7.62mm NATO rounds very accurately due to its bolt action and thermal shielded barrel.
szBRDesc: The deadliest French representative since Napoleon, albeit completely opposite in its stature.  This ambitious sniper rifle fires 7.62mm NATO rounds very accurately due to its bolt action and thermal shielded barrel.

szItemDesc: The Galil AR from Israel is related to Valmet M76. In fact, the first prototypes were designed from blueprints bought from Valmet.
szBRDesc: The Galil assault rifle is designed for heavy combat. Reliability and lethality in one package.

szItemDesc: This is the shortened version of the Galil, easier to handle for paratroopers and mechanized troops.
szBRDesc: This is the shortened version of the Galil AR. It is easier to handle for troops that are used to work under tight conditions.

szItemDesc: There are big guns, there are big, big guns, and then there's this gun. Bring shoulder pads.
szBRDesc: Ugly as sin, but so what? Whether it's knocking the treads off a tank or popping an enemy combatant like a water balloon, this gun makes it easy to feel like God.

szItemDesc: A slightly more compact version of the model 17, the model 19 gives you the same reliable 9mm Glock action.
szBRDesc: A slightly more compact version of the model 17, the model 19 gives you the same reliable 9mm Glock action.

szItemDesc: A bull-pup design of the AKS-74U in 7.62mm WP.  This particular variant has a built-in GP-25 grenade launcher.
szBRDesc: The Groza is a neat little weapon, but not recommended for lefties due the placement of its cocking handle, selector switch and ejection port.  This variant comes with an integral GP-25 40mm grenade launcher.

szItemDesc: Putting a silencer on this already subsonic rifle can help you keep a low profile and stay stylish in any urban combat enviroment.
szBRDesc: Putting a silencer on this already subsonic rifle can help you keep a low profile and stay stylish in any urban combat enviroment. Fires 9x39mm Subsonic ammo that is highly armor effective.

szItemDesc: The HK 23E is a light 5.56mm NATO MG and is of the same quality one would expect from Heckler and Koch.
szBRDesc: The manufacturer's name says it all.  We highly recommend the HK 23E. It's reliable and does the job effectively with 100-rounds in a Beta C-Mag. Includes bipod.

szItemDesc: Combine the best features of the G36 and the M4 with Heckler & Koch's HK416.
szBRDesc: After fixing England's SA80, now Heckler & Koch wants to improve America's M4. The HK416 is available in both an upgrade kit for M4s or as a complete weapon with a HK made lower receiver.

szItemDesc: A personal defence weapon designed to compliment the G11 rifle, the G11 PDW was rumored to only be in the prototype phase.
szBRDesc: SPECIAL!  Available for a limited time only: G11 sidearm prototypes with glow-in-the-dark keychain!

szItemDesc: The G36 is a conventional gas operated, selective fire rifle, made from mostly modern materials and using mostly modern technologies.  The G36C is the compact version.
szBRDesc: The G36 is a conventional gas operated, selective fire rifle, made from mostly modern materials and using mostly modern technologies.  The G36C is the compact or commando version.

szItemDesc: The G36 RAS is a conventional gas operated, selective fire rifle, made from mostly modern materials and using mostly modern technologies.
szBRDesc: The G36 RAS is a conventional gas operated, selective fire rifle, using mostly modern materials and technologies. Unlike the 'E'-version, the 'RAS' is outfitted with Picatinny rails.

szItemDesc: The G36 RAS is a conventional gas operated, selective fire rifle, using mostly modern materials and technologies.  The G36K RAS is the carbine version.
szBRDesc: The G36 RAS is a conventional gas operated, selective fire rifle, using mostly modern materials and technologies.  The G36K RAS is the carbine version.

szItemDesc: The smallest G3 variant, the G3KA4 features a 12.4 inch barrel, but is still chambered for the same 7.62mm rounds as its bigger brother.
szBRDesc: A smaller version of the venerable G3, this baby packs a killer right hook at both ends. The recoil of these rifles is almost as legendary as their stopping power

szItemDesc: Not as bulky or heavy as other LMG's, this gun still has a rate of fire that will frappe an enemy in no time.
szBRDesc: HK has blessed us with their new versatile, multi-role squad machine gun. This version is outfitted with Picatinny rails.

szItemDesc: The latest LMG from HK is gas-operated, belt-fed, and air-cooled.  An integral bipod and RIS rails give you lots of room for addons.
szBRDesc: First shown in 2001 in London, the all-new MG43 continues HK's long standing tradition of fine weaponry. Comes standard with integral bipod. Since 2006 it's introduced in the Bundeswehr (German Army) as the MG4.

szItemDesc: A large pistol designed to meet the exacting requirements of the US Special Operations Command.
szBRDesc: A large pistol designed to meet the exacting requirements of the US Special Operations Command.  If it's good enough for SOCOM, it's good enough for you!

szItemDesc: This is yet another version of the tried and true MP5, by H&K. Chambered in 10mm, it's a compromise between extreme controlability and increased firepower.
szBRDesc: The MP5A2's bigger, badder brother. Bringing the impressive 10mm cartridge to bear, this SMG bridges the gap between an MP5 and the UMP-45, and is choice in CQB!

szItemDesc: A modern SMG for the old Tokarev round.
szBRDesc: The latest and most modern SMG for the 7.62x25mm round. Comes with integrated folding stock and lasersight in the forward handguard.

szItemDesc: The MP7 is a compact submachine gun with folding forward grip and telescoped buttstock, and is designed to fire special, high velocity 4.6mm ammunition.
szBRDesc: The MP7 is a compact submachine gun with folding forward grip and telescoped buttstock, and is designed to fire special, high velocity 4.6mm ammunition.

szItemDesc: The MSG-90 sniper rifle was made by Heckler-Koch as a "militarized" offspring of their PSG-1 police sniper rifle.
szBRDesc: The MSG-90 sniper rifle was made by Heckler-Koch as a "militarized" offspring of their PSG-1 police sniper rifle.  The MSG-90A1 is fitted with the barrel threaded on the muzzle to accept screw-on silencers.

szItemDesc: The P7 pistols are known for their low barrel axis and slim profile, which makes them accurate and easily concealable pistols.
szBRDesc: The P7 pistols are known for their low barrel axis and slim profile, which makes them accurate and easily concealable pistols. They also are somewhat expensive, but have a strong following among many shooters.

szItemDesc: Quiet and deadly, this gun screams to become part of any covert operation you might have on the drawing board.
szBRDesc: Leave it to HK to design a gun that gives new meaning to the phrase "silent but deadly." We love those guys.

szItemDesc: The UMP (Universal Machinen-Pistole = Universal Submachine Gun) was developed by the Heckler & Koch company of Germany in the mid- to late- 1990s.
szBRDesc: The UMP (Universal Machinen-Pistole = Universal Submachine Gun) was developed by the Heckler & Koch company of Germany in the mid- to late- 1990s.

szItemDesc: The HK USP (Universal Self-loading Pistol) appeared in 1993.  It is a serious combat/self defence weapon.
szBRDesc: The HK USP (Universal Self-loading Pistol) appeared in 1993, designed to be a police and military sidearm. All USP pistols are built on the same modified Browning linkless locked breech action with patented recoil reduction system.

szItemDesc: The archtypal pump-action shotgun. In three quarters of a century of production, it has lost none of its potency.
szBRDesc: Few things make a potential enemy vacate the premises like a solid, reliable shotgun. Chamber a round in the middle of a crowd and watch em' fight to maintain bowel control.

szItemDesc: The Pancor Jackhammer fires 10 rounds of 12 gauge ammo in less than 10 seconds, giving a whole new meaning to the term "pumped full of lead".
szBRDesc: As the poster child of auto-shotguns, the Pancor Jackhammer is proof that almost all problems CAN be solved with violence.

szItemDesc: This Finnish SMG from the 80's may be remembered from movies such as Cobra and Red Dawn.
szBRDesc: The Jati-Matic is sleek and easily concealed. Just squeeze the trigger harder for full auto!

szItemDesc: This anti-material bolt-action sniper rifle comes from Russia. Its effect on enemy troops can best be described by two words: bloody mess.
szBRDesc: In skilled hands this heavy sniper rifle never fails to deliver. And now it's on discount!

szItemDesc: A Rugged and dependable semi-automatic, just watch your thumbs when reloading.
szBRDesc: The first self-loading rifle to be adopted by any army, the M1 has seen service from Normandy and Guadalcanal to the Chosin Reservoir and Khe Sahn and beyond.

szItemDesc: The M21 tactical rifle is the sniper version of the M14.  An accurate rifle with good stopping power.
szBRDesc: The M21 sniper rifle is a semi-automatic version of the M14, and is fitted with a longer barrel for increased range and accuracy.

szItemDesc: Standard issue sniper rifle with the US Marine Corps.  Highly accurate with good penetration and stopping power.
szBRDesc: SPECIAL PRICE!  The USMC standard issue M40A1 sniper rifle of the is being replaced by the M40A3, which means we are receiving more shipments of these babies than we can handle and they all must go!  Get one for yourself, one for your old lady and one for your kid!

szItemDesc: Wet or dry, Metal Storm's Surf Zone SMG will not jam. Just be sure to have someone good with electronics around to fix it.
szBRDesc: Metal Storm's obscene rate of fire is always an attention grabber. Featherweight reliable mass firepower sells it. It makes sense that the Surf Zone is secured by an electronic fingerprint lock.

szItemDesc: The M60E3 is a smaller, lighter and improved version of the legendary M60 light machinegun used by the US Armed Forces.
szBRDesc: Always wanted to be like Rambo?  Now you can!  With the M60E3, you'll always look good taking out a drug cartel, mowing down local mob bosses, and stopping an entire invasion force on your own. Comes with integral bipod and foregrip.

szItemDesc: Quick firing, ugly, and functional. The M11/9 is as reminiscent of the 1980s as bad music and cocaine fueled business decisions. Not to be mistaken for a M11, though.
szBRDesc: A first choice among many on both sides of the law for close-quarters dispatch with negliable penetration. The 1200rpm cyclic rate makes for a lot of muzzle climb, so aim low.

szItemDesc: The Makarov PM is a post-WW2 Soviet Army pistol, and while it's not the most powerful weapon around, it's still fairly reliable.
szBRDesc: The Makarov PM (Pistolet Makarova) evolved from the post-WW2 Soviet Army requirements for a new pistol: more compact, more safe and with greater stopping power than the then-standard Tokarev TT-33 pistol.

szItemDesc: A modified version of the Makarov PM, developed during the 1990's.
szBRDesc: A modified version of the Makarov PM, developed during the 1990's.  This model attempts to address the original's deficiences: small clip size and low stopping power.

szItemDesc: Known throughout the middle east as the MAR Tactical, the Micro Galil is IMI's latest and most compact entry in the Galil family of assault weapons.
szBRDesc: A redesigned version of Galil MAR, with a completely new, thicker and much better protecting hand guard, a carbon-fibre folding stock instead of a steel one, and an extra standard rail.

szItemDesc: Little brother to the world-famous SMG, this diminutive devil deals death at 950rpm.
szBRDesc: The Mini-Uzi provides tremendous firepower in a travel sized package.

szItemDesc: The Mosin Nagant was the standard infantry weapon for the defenders of the motherland from 1891 until the late 1940s.
szBRDesc: Used by snipers from Stalingrad to Saigon, budding Zaitsevs everywhere will love the Mosin-Nagant.

szItemDesc: Versatile pump-action shotgun manufactured by the Russian arms company Baikal.
szBRDesc: For decades, Baikal has been designing and producing excellent shotguns.

szItemDesc: One of the newest handgun models in use in the Russian military, the Varjag features a frame made from super strong thermosetting plastic material.
szBRDesc: One of the newest handgun models in use in the Russian military, the Varjag features a frame made from super strong thermosetting plastic material.

szItemDesc: The best thing to come out of South Africa since Apartheid ended, you can be sure Nelson Mandela didn't have this one in mind.
szBRDesc: This unique 12 gauge features a bullpup design, a rear feeding tube magazine, and a new forward-back pump method.

szItemDesc: This Russian monstrosity is a counter-sniper/antimaterial rifle.  At nearly 2m in length, this rifle is also useful for polevaulting.
szBRDesc: This Russian monstrosity is a counter-sniper/antimaterial rifle.  At nearly 2m in length, this rifle is also useful for polevaulting.

szItemDesc: Whether you're hunting deer or other snipers, the M82 is a solid bet. It has a reputation for staying accurate at distances well beyond 400 meters.
szBRDesc: This sniper rifles comes with iron sights, adjustable trigger, and a rotating bolt. Designed in 1982, it has proven so formidable that it's currently still in service with the British, Canadian, New Zealand, and Australian armed forces.

szItemDesc: The Pecheneg machine gun is an upgraded PKM.  It's currently in limited production and has been issued on trial basis for some Russian troops in Chechnya. The barrel is not quick-detachable.
szBRDesc: An upgraded PKM, the Pecheneg is slightly lighter and has a higher rate of fire. The barrel is not quick-detachable.

szItemDesc: The PKM is the Russian eqvivalent of the US M60.  It's a universal MG that fires the heavy Russian 7.62x54mm round instead of the 7.62x39mm WP.
szBRDesc: Around since the 1960s, the PKM is one of the most famous Russian MGs and is used all over the world.  Now you have the chance to show your enemies that old school Soviet weapons are still superior!

szItemDesc: Smoother than fine vodka, the PP-93 is a favorite among Russian police and security forces.
szBRDesc: A true machine-pistol, the PP-93 offers compact concealability in a slim, stamped metal package.

szItemDesc: Feared and respected among SMGs for its range and rate of fire, the PPsh is the tommy gun's hulking Eastern cousin.
szBRDesc: Known as the "Burp-gun" for the sound produced by its high cyclic rate, the PPsh-41 belches death at 900rpm.

szItemDesc: Designed as a backup weapon for Soviet officers, the PSM is an ultra-light, ultra-fast weapon with low to moderate stopping power.
szBRDesc: The PSM was designed in 1970s as a self-defence firearm for top commanders in the Soviet armed forces.  It is an ultra-light, ultra-fast weapon with low stopping power.

szItemDesc: This export version of the Chinese assault rifle attempts to further tip the trade balance in China's favor, but when all's said and done, it's still "Made in China".
szBRDesc: This export version of the Chinese assault rifle attempts to further tip the trade balance in China's favor, although the annoying little features of this gun (no provision for lefties, high sights, and an odd selector switch) certainly earn it the stamp "Made in China".

szItemDesc: Throughout its mass-production, the Russian made RPD underwent four model revisions, none of which included a select fire mode. The barrel is not quick-detachable.
szBRDesc: Its full-auto bark has been heard in nearly every corner of the globe. If you need a squad automatic, look no further. The barrel is not quick-detachable.

szItemDesc: Another product of Mikhail Kalashnikov, from Russia with love. The barrel is not quick-detachable.
szBRDesc: The RPK is essentially an AK-47 with a heavier barrel and stock. It can empty a 30 round magazine or a 75 round drum at 600rpm. The barrel is not quick-detachable.

szItemDesc: Please read the following out loud, in a gravelly voice:  A Ruger Redhawk revolver, in good condition, with six bullets left.
szBRDesc: The Super Redhawk is ideal for sportsmen using a handgun to hunt big game, and is also popular among metallic silhouette shooters.  This revolver is world-renowned for strength, safety, and rugged reliability.

szItemDesc: Those crazy Czechs and their designations. This time, under their term for SMG there hides a full-power assault rifle.
szBRDesc: In case you want a 7.62mm WP assault rifle, reconsider your decision to get a cheap AK clone made in someone's backyard. Take this Czech rifle instead, it may cost a bit more, but it also offers higher quality.

szItemDesc: The TRG-22 is used by the governments of several nations as their primary sniper rifle.
szBRDesc: The Finnish Sako sniper rifles are known by their world-class accuracy and strength. Order yours today!

szItemDesc: The TRG-42 is the big brother of the TRG series and is used as a long-range precision tool by special forces around the world.
szBRDesc: The TRG-42 in .338 Lapua Mag will meet the demands of the most demanding tactical snipers.

szItemDesc: Gunfighters from Doc Holiday to Bonnie Parker have valued the wide dispersal and raw destructive power of a truncated scatter-gun.
szBRDesc: Nothing else ends a gunfight (and leaves a terrible mess) faster. Get it for that special someone in your life.

szItemDesc: The 7.62mm NATO brother model to the SIG540, the SG542 is standard army issue in many nations.
szBRDesc: Swiss-made weapons are the standard for dependability, and the SG542 is no exception.

szItemDesc: A Swiss 5.56mm rifle with removable bipod and integral flash suppressor, this one will leave your enemies like dairy products of a similar nationality.
szBRDesc: A Swiss 5.56mm rifle with removable bipod and integral flash suppressor, this one will leave your enemies like dairy products of a similar nationality.

szItemDesc: The shorter barrel of this SIG 550 variant is a heck of a lot more convenient in close quarters.
szBRDesc: The shorter barrel of this SIG 550 variant is a heck of a lot more convenient in closer quarters. Includes flash suppressor.

szItemDesc: The scaled down version of the SIG 550, this 5.56mm carbine is excellent for CQB, with integrated flash hider and removable bipod.
szBRDesc: The 552 is a extraordinarily well made carbine. Equipped with a side folding skeletonized stock and a flash suppressor.  Order one now and get a free folding bipod with purchase!

szItemDesc: The SIG P210 was developed by Schweizerische Industrie Gesellschaft (SIG) in 1938-1945, and was adopted by the Swiss Military in 1949
szBRDesc: The SIG P210 was developed by Schweizerische Industrie Gesellschaft (SIG) in 1938-1945, and was adopted by the Swiss Military in 1949.  The P210 is a recoil-operated, locked breech handgun with slightly modified Browning HI-Power style barrel locking.

szItemDesc: The SIG P226 first appeared in 1983, and is the official sidearm of the US Navy SEALs. This particular pistol has been re-chambered for a .40 S&W round and has a Picatinny Rail.
szBRDesc: The SIG P226 first appeared in 1983, and is the official sidearm of the US Navy SEALs. This variant has been re-chambered for the .40 S&W round and has a Picatinny Rail.

szItemDesc: A modernized version of the P228 with a short rail.
szBRDesc: This is a modernized version of the P228. It is available in several different calibers (this is the 9x19mm version) and has a short Picatinny Rail in front of the triggerguard.

szItemDesc: The SIG Pro pistol represents the latest advances in modern handgun technology. It is one of the most reliable handguns available today.
szBRDesc: The SIG Pro pistol represents the latest advances in modern handgun technology.  Lightweight and requiring no maintenance, it is one of the most reliable pistols available.

szItemDesc: Offering the same stealthiness but requiring less money, this weapon is a competitor to both MicroUZI and MP-5K.
szBRDesc: Loved and used both by counter-terrorist forces and by terrorists, this weapon packs a significant close-range punch for its size and cost.

szItemDesc: Like anything Swiss-made, it's finely crafted, dependable, and expensive.
szBRDesc: The Sphinx 3000 is more than suitable for competitive match shooting or service applications.

szItemDesc: A reliable pistol of Croatian design, the XD is for use in harsh environments.
szBRDesc: A quite reliable pistol, this is a Croatian design for use in harsh environments. Testimonial from Hamous of Metavira: "Me like that gun!"

szItemDesc: The 9x21mm round used by this Makarov clone was specially designed to pierce Kevlar AND Titanium plates at 100 meters.
szBRDesc: The 9x21mm round used by this Makarov clone was specially designed to pierce Kevlar AND Titanium plates at 100 meters.  This long forgotten Russian Pistole is now the side arm of choice for the Russian Federation.

szItemDesc: Designed in the 1950s, the APS is not the most accurate weapon, but is still one of the fastest machine pistols around today.
szBRDesc: The APS is surprisingly fast for a weapon of its size, and is invaluable in mopping up any messes from when sh*t hits the fan.

szItemDesc: This SMG provided more than fifty years of reliability and accuracy to British armed forces.
szBRDesc: This SMG provided more than fifty years of reliability and accuracy to British armed forces.

szItemDesc: A heavier barrel and integral bipod transform the AUG into a hardy squad automatic.
szBRDesc: Otherwise very similar to the AUG, the HBAR features a heavier barrel, integral bipod and can use larger magazines.

szItemDesc: A shortened AUG chambered to fire 9mm rounds in a tidy, bullpup configuration.
szBRDesc: A shortened AUG chambered to fire 9mm rounds in a tidy, bullpup configuration.

szItemDesc: A shorty snipersystem, accurate to 1 MOA over 500 yards. This small rifle fires a big bullet, and does it very well.
szBRDesc: Looking for a lightweight, compact, accurate, easy to use sniper rifle? Look no further! This bolt action .308 is the size of a carbine, and packs a wallop, even from a few hundred meters.

szItemDesc: Whether you're hunting deer or other snipers, the SSG-P1 is a solid bet.
szBRDesc: Cousin Lester took this gun out shooting for the elk hunt last year...then he took it out when his daughter came home pregnant. He bagged both bucks at over 600 yards.

szItemDesc: A compact machine-pistol from the Steyr family, this Austrian SMG features a compact, comfortable design that is easy to control.
szBRDesc: The TMP is the perfect compromise between firepower and concealability.

szItemDesc: Control riots with this 12 round semi-auto shotgun like never before.
szBRDesc: This is the US made version of the South-African Striker shotgun. The key advantage of this shotgun is its large magazine capacity, but it is slow to reload.

szItemDesc: Major firepower in a mean little package, the Serbu Firearms Mini-Shotgun is perfect for home-defense or the ultimate hold-out weapon.
szBRDesc: Want a cut-down scattergun in the worst way? With Serbu's Super-Shorty you can forgo time-consuming hacksaw work.

szItemDesc: A new Russian military sniper rifle intended for elite units. Maintenance on the barrel is important on this one!
szBRDesc: We were able to get a few of these new Russian sniper rifles. Please state if you want a wooden or fiberglass stock.

szItemDesc: This quintessential Russian sniper rifle has proven its worth on battlefields all over the globe.
szBRDesc: The Dragunov has been deadly in the hands of snipers for nearly 40 years.  The SVDS is the smaller, but heavier, cousin of the SVD.

szItemDesc: The Snaiperskaya Vintovka Ukorochennay, Short Sniper Rifle is a shortened variant of the famous Dragunov sniper rifle with bull-pup configuration.
szBRDesc: This rifle is more compact and has somewhat shorter effective range than the SVD. It's also more silent since the muzzle also has a flash hider and noise decreaser.

szItemDesc: The features that tamed the world's most powerful revolver cartridge make shooting the popular .44 Magnum load a pleasure.
szBRDesc: The features that tamed the world's most powerful revolver cartridge make shooting the popular .44 Magnum load a pleasure.  Add Taurus' rock-steady scope mount base and your favorite rings and optics to make your Raging Bull a venerable hunter.

szItemDesc: Venerated by the same mobsters it ventilated, the 1928A1 is by no means a museum piece, having roared its way out of the roaring twenties and beyond.
szBRDesc: Employed by gangsters and G-Men alike, the Tommy gun's status as an antique shouldn't deter modern users from making use of its firepower.

szItemDesc: Developed in the late 1920's, this pistol was the official side arm of the Red Army in WW2.
szBRDesc: Developed in the late 1920's, this pistol was the official side arm of the Red Army in WW2.  For its time, the TT was a formidable weapon, with good penetration and range.

szItemDesc: The large caliber Udar revolver is commonly used by private security agencies and other organisations involved in special missions.
szBRDesc: A large caliber (12.5 mm) revolver with high stopping power, used by private security forces and on special operations.

szItemDesc: Designed and produced in Singapore, the Ultimax 100 LMG line fires either drum or box magazines of 5.56mm ammo.
szBRDesc: Reliable and comparatively light-weight, our ST Kinetics' Ultimaxes have been modified to accept 5.56mm Beta C-Mags. Comes with integral bipod and foregrip.

szItemDesc: Capable of fully automatic fire, the USAS-12 is designed to provide sustained firepower in close combat scenarios.
szBRDesc: Capable of fully automatic fire, the USAS-12 is designed to provide sustained firepower in close combat scenarios.

szItemDesc: The Valmet M76 is almost an identical copy of the Rk 62, a high quality AK-47 clone that was developed for the Finnish Defence Forces.
szBRDesc: This Valmet M76 made from high quality steel and plastic parts is one of the best AK-47 assault rifle variants in the world.

szItemDesc: A variant of the famed Finnish assault rifle, this model features a polymer body and is chambered for a 5.56mm round.
szBRDesc: Originally constructed on the AK's internal works, this hardy weapon can stand up to tons of abuse.

szItemDesc: The VIS-35 was the standard issue sidearm of the Polish military in WW2.  It is still manufactured today in limited quantities for collectors.
szBRDesc: The VIS-35 was the standard issue sidearm of the Polish military in WW2.  It is still manufactured today in limited quantities for collectors.  According to some sources, it is one of the best handguns ever built.

szItemDesc: Cheaper, lower quality cousin of the VSS Vintorez, this silenced gun can still be your best friend in any situation requiring stealth, firepower, and attitude.
szBRDesc: This silenced sniper rifle is made by a company known for manufacturing aircraft cannons and anti-tank missiles. Who could ask for anything more? Oh, and did we mention it can go full auto?

szItemDesc: Sometimes considered the Ferrari of sniper rifles, the WA 2000 combines high accuracy with great stopping power.  Too bad they're no longer in production.
szBRDesc: Now back in stock!  The WA 2000 is no longer in production, but we were able to locate a few, and they're on sale for the low, low price of only $7940! Get yours now while supplies last!

szItemDesc: Winchester Rifles have been knocking rustlers and varmints out of the saddle for more than a century.
szBRDesc: Through range wars and gunfights the Winchester rifle has always been a solid choice.

szItemDesc: The XM-29 is part 20mm magazine fed grenade launcher, part G36 5.56mm assault rifle, and all kinds of whoop-ass.
szBRDesc: The XM-29 is a combination weapon, part 20mm magazine fed grenade launcher and part 5.56mm assault rifle.  Both parts are assembled into the single one-man portable unit with a built-in target acquisition / fire control system (TA/FCS).

szItemDesc: This 5.56 assault platform fills a variety of roles. Ever wanted to serve someone a lead salad? Point at enemy and pull trigger to taste.
szBRDesc: Originally commissioned by the U.S. military, HK is now producing this 5.56 multi-role weapon for the highest bidder. Lucky you.

szItemDesc: The XM-8 is HK's response to the USA's call for a new standard Army rifle. The BLC version is the standard, and offers a versatile array of options.
szBRDesc: The new XM-8 family of weapons is spearheading the "next gen" infantry weapons movement, after the OICW contract went belly up.

szItemDesc: The Compact is a shorty version of the XM-8, outfitted specifically for short range engagements, notably urban ops.
szBRDesc: The Compact is a shorty version of the XM-8, outfitted specifically for short range engagements, notably urban ops.

szItemDesc: The Sharpshooter version of the XM-8 is the Next Gen DMR, featuring a much longer, match grade, long-twist barrel for accuracy over longer ranges.
szBRDesc: The Sharpshooter version of the XM-8 is the Next Gen DMR, featuring a much longer, match grade, long-twist barrel for accuracy over longer ranges.

szItemDesc: A Serbian conversion of the classic AK-47, a semiautomatic sniper rifle that is relatively accurate, yet antiquated.
szBRDesc: A Serbian conversion of the classic AK-47, a semiautomatic sniper rifle that is relatively accurate, yet antiquated.

szItemDesc: Russian made over-and-under double barreled shotgun.
szBRDesc: One of the many finely produced sporting shotguns on the market from Baikal.

szItemDesc: The G36 is a conventional gas operated, selective fire rifle.  This non-export model comes standard with a built-in reflex scope.
szBRDesc: The G36 is a conventional gas operated, selective fire rifle, made from mostly modern materials and using mostly modern technologies.  This non-export model comes standard with a built-in reflex scope.

szItemDesc: The G36K is the carbine version of the G36.  This non-export comes standard with a built-in reflex scope.
szBRDesc: The G36 is a conventional gas operated, selective fire rifle, made from mostly modern materials and using mostly modern technologies.  The G36K is the carbine version, and comes standard with a built-in reflex scope.

szItemDesc: The development of this rifle probably went like this: "We take a bit from every other AR on the market, and mash them all together."
szBRDesc: Influenced by a lot of different designs, the rifle version of the Indian Small Arms System is a fine Assault Rifle as well.

szItemDesc: Competitor to the .50 AE variant of the Desert Eagle.
szBRDesc: A competitor to the .50 AE Desert Eagle, and a fine American piece of work.

szItemDesc: French Army pistol with an unusual locking mechanism.
szBRDesc: Discontinued when MAB went out of business. Buy while stocks last.

szItemDesc: Designed to slay "monsters" in a single blow, the .50 Beowulf rifle from Alexander Arms will make you a legend in your own time; heroic deeds are just moments away - let the ballads begin.
szBRDesc: Use what the U.S Coast Guard uses: they know what they're doing.

szItemDesc: This SMG was in use by German police before they switched to HK weapons (around 1985).
szBRDesc: Surplus weapons for the serious gun collector. The MPL was used extensively by German police forces prior to 1985.

szItemDesc: The improved version of the M16. Modified due to experience from Vietnam.
szBRDesc: The M16's deficiencies began to dissolve with this model. Ammo was now loaded with powders that produce much less residue in the gun action. Barrel, chamber, and bolt are chrome-lined to improve corrosion resistance.

szItemDesc: The shortened version of the M16, favored by special forces in Vietnam.
szBRDesc: Initially, the CAR-15 showed some problems. First, it was too loud. Second, the muzzle flash was also terrific. Colt partially solved this problem by installing a new, longer flash suppressor. This model was officially adopted as the XM177-E1.

szItemDesc: You will forget the Desert Eagle and any "highpower" revolvers when you have shot with this one.
szBRDesc: New CMMG 7.3"Pistol w/Four Rail. Features a chrome lined 1/7" twist, 5.56mm barrel. Other features include feed cut ramp, padded pistol buffer assy, sling adapter, and T marked receiver. Lifetime warranty.

szItemDesc: This is a cut down M16 that has been made into a pistol. It uses a free-floating barrel and will also accept standard M16 magazines.
szBRDesc: In production for over a decade now. This model uses the OA operations system which incorporates the recoil system into the upper receiver, eliminating the need for an extension tube or buttstock.

szItemDesc: A large pistol in .45 Winchester Magnum caliber, made by Galena Industries.
szBRDesc: The .45 Winchester Magnum version of Galena's line of Automag pistols.

szItemDesc: This version of the Grizzly pistol existed before the .50 AE variant was made.
szBRDesc: The Grizzly pistols are based on the Colt 1911, as their looks already told you, but they have been beefed up to shoot stronger ammo.

szItemDesc: A longbarreled .45 Winchester Magnum pistol.
szBRDesc: If you are seeing red, do like Charles Bronson did: Pack this one!

szItemDesc: This is a DMR-version of the C7-rifle, with built-in bipod and sound suppressor.
szBRDesc: The C7 "Custom Tactical" is a designated marksman rifle suitable for the spotter of a sniper/spotter-team.

szItemDesc: The Contender pistol exists in a wide variety of calibers, this one is chambered for .454 Casull.
szBRDesc: The Thompson Contender Encore is a one-shot targetpistol that can also be used for hunting, if equipped with a suitable scope. Chambered for .454 Casull, this is a most powerful gun.

szItemDesc: The preferred backup weapon of big-game hunters, though it can be a little rough on your wrist.
szBRDesc: The Ruger Super Redhawk Alaskan is a snubnosed .454 Casull revolver, a neat "little" surprise to anyone who wants you ill.

szItemDesc: A retro-style revolver, in a not-so-retro caliber.
szBRDesc: The Freedom Arms Model 83 Premier Grade may look like one of the very first revolvers that used cartridges, but it is quite new, and fires the all-powerful .454 Casull ammo.

szItemDesc: Designed by Aimo Lahti, this accurate if heavy SMG is a well-made, elementary blowback weapon. In appearance it is very similar to the German Bergmann MP34 and the Soviet PPD 1934G/38G and PPSh41 which it inspired.
szBRDesc: The Suomi was used with great sucess during the war of 1940 against the Soviet Union, where this SMG showed the importance of SMGs to modern warfare. Manufacture of the Suomi ceased in 1944, but Finland used it well into the 1990s, when finally it was replaced by assault rifles.

szItemDesc: A very special sniper rifle that comes with integral silencer, integral bipod, and fires subsonic AP ammunition.
szBRDesc: Quite new on the market, the Russian Vychlop (which means 'Exhaust') coughs up something more substantial (and more deadly) than carbon monoxide. Comes with integral bipod plus PKS-07 Scope.

szItemDesc: Designed as a police weapon from the ground up, it was introduced in 1979.
szBRDesc: A semi-automatic shotgun designed for police use and Hollywood action movies. For lighter loads and special ammunition switch to pump-action.

szItemDesc: The standard rifle of the German army during World War II. Rifles made after 1942 may have cheaper furniture and fittings, but the Germans never went cheap on barrel, bolt, and action.
szBRDesc: This well constructed carbine version of the Gewehr 98 was Germany's standard rifle during World War II. Price is for guns of later production runs, earlier rifles on order. Ammo in stripper clips can be found in the Ammo-section.

szItemDesc: The R1 is another beautiful design by Benelli, and uses comfort tech to dampen recoil. Also comes with a picatinny rail for easy scope replacements. This .300 WinMag model uses a 5 round clip.
szBRDesc: The Benelli R1 is another semi-automatic competitor on the sniper rifle market, and a beautifully designed one.

szItemDesc: This .300 WinMag bolt-action rifle uses straight-pull technology to make chambering a new round a bit faster.
szBRDesc: The Blaser R93 Tactical is another futuristic german design. It has a quick interchangeable system that allows for swaping barrels without the need to resight the scope. This .300 WinMag model is used widely by German and Dutch police.

szItemDesc: A straight-pull bolt-action rifle with a futuristic look. Pull back pistolgrip to chamber a new round, but take care of your triggerfinger: the triggerguard moves as well, but the trigger does not!
szBRDesc: The S&O Shorty is a straight-pull bolt-action bullpup design with a very unique action: to chamber a new round, you pull the pistolgrip. It's made for hunting, despite the futuristic look. And if you're hunting the most dangerous animal of all, then it can also act as a mid range sniper rifle.

szItemDesc: In production from 1949-1968, this Czech SMG has been liberally supplied to revolutionaries all over the world.
szBRDesc: An older Czech SMG that fires the Russian 7.62x25mm cartridge. It is claimed that it will also fire the 7.63 Mauser pistol cartridge.

szItemDesc: This version of the SAR 21 has Picatinny rails instead of a fixed optical sight and built-in laser aiming device, so you can choose how to equip it.
szBRDesc: This version of the SAR 21 bullpup assault rifle has several attachment points and is considered more versatile compared to the standard model.

szItemDesc: Developed for Special Forces to enable using battlefield pick-up magazines, this gun is essentially a M4 chambered for 7.62x39mm.
szBRDesc: If the Russians make some of their guns in NATO calibers, we can do it the other way around. Developed for tunnel-fighting and using AK-47 magazines, this 7.62x39mm M4-variant comes with a sound suppressor. Only very few available..

szItemDesc: Made with a synthetic frame and with hammerless action, this is obviously a competitor to the Glock pistols.
szBRDesc: If it is good enough for James Bond, it is surely good enough for you. Commemorative models available on order.

szItemDesc: A hunting rifle using Germany's WW-II rifle caliber.
szBRDesc: The bolt-action system of the old Mauser Kar98k lives on in this hunting rifle. Comes with a 7x magnification scope.

szItemDesc: Variant of the AKMS, which is a variant of the standard AKM. Was made shorter for special units and paratroopers. U-shaped buttplate of folding stock allows folding/unfolding while a magazine is inserted.
szBRDesc: This even more shortened variant of the AKM comes with a folding stock that allows folding/unfolding while a magazine is in the gun. It was developed for paratroopers and special units, and is quite functional despite the rather unusual foregrip.

szItemDesc: A Colt semiautomatic chambered for the 10mm Auto cartridge.
szBRDesc: Colt's entry into the 10mm pistol market. All you expect from a Colt pistol, and more.

szItemDesc: The SCAR is FN's newest offering into the military armament scene. The "H" stands for "Heavy", and refers to this version firing the 7.62mm NATO round. This is the sniper variant.
szBRDesc: Not for sale through BR.

szItemDesc: FN's latest addition to the SCAR family is the "L" or Light version, chambered in 5.56mm NATO. This is the sniper variant.
szBRDesc: Not for sale through BR.

szItemDesc: The Advanced Combat Rifle fires a small armor penetrating fin stabilized dart over a considerable range.
szBRDesc: Prototype of a new generation of assault rifles, the Steyr ACR fires fin stabilized darts. This is the future weapon of choice.

szItemDesc: The SCAR is FN's newest offering into the military armament scene. The "WP" refers to this version firing the 7.62mm WP round. CQC denotes the shortest version for fighting in dense terrain.
szBRDesc: Not for sale through BR.

szItemDesc: The SCAR is FN's newest offering into the military armament scene. The "WP" refers to this version firing the 7.62mm WP round. This is the sniper variant.
szBRDesc: Not for sale through BR.

szItemDesc: This CQC version of the SCAR-L has been converted to fire the 6.8mm SPC round.
szBRDesc: Not for sale through BR.

szItemDesc: This sniper variant of the SCAR-L has been converted for the new 6.8x43mm SPC round.
szBRDesc: Not for sale through BR.

szItemDesc: Yet another version of the H&K MP5, chambered in .40 S&W.
szBRDesc: The more popular of the new caliber MP5's, this is the .40 S&W version

szItemDesc: Barrett's entry into the 6.8mm SPC rifle market. A strong and sturdy rifle.
szBRDesc: Not what you usually expect when you hear 'Barrett', but rest assured that this 6.8mm SPC rifle has the usual high quality and precision of any other Barrett rifle.

szItemDesc: The Bushmaster M4A3, chambered for the new 6.8mm SPC round.
szBRDesc: Bushmaster's famous M4A3, now in 6.8mm SPC. As an added bonus, this is the military/LE full-auto variant.

szItemDesc: The Robinson Armament XCR-1 is just another M4 clone in 6.8mm SPC.
szBRDesc: Another new entry on the 6.8mm SPC market, the XCR-1 comes with a folding stock, which looks a bit unusual on a M4 clone, but works very well.

szItemDesc: Standard sidearm of the German Army during WW-II. It is also known as the "Luger".
szBRDesc: A somewhat complicated pistol for the serious gun collector. Be careful when taking it apart. Call us for spare parts.

szItemDesc: The reduced snag version of the P226 pistol.
szBRDesc: Reliability and ease of use are key features of this swiss made handgun. Improved with the SIG-Anti-Snag system.

szItemDesc: A version of the P226, chambered in .40 S&W, with rounded edges to reduce snag and facilitate easier concealed carry.
szBRDesc: A stainless steel slide and the SIG-Anti-Snag system (for easier concealed carrying) are improvements over the standard version.

szItemDesc: Dyneema UD full composite helmets provide the highest degree of protection at less weight than alternative materials, against both flying shrapnel and bullets.
szBRDesc: "BOOM! Headshot!" Who cares? With this helmet you are protected from bullets and you'll still score with the ladies.

szItemDesc: Produced under license by several companies, Dyneema fabric is 40 percent stronger than Kevlar.
szBRDesc: Some wearers describe Dyneema fabric leggings as uncomfortable; however, stopping a bullet with one's unprotected groin would be considerably less enjoyable.

szItemDesc: Dyneema UD-based vests provide maximum protection at an extremely low weight. Together with the high flexibility of Dyneema UD, this translates into high wearing comfort for the individual user, ensuring that mercs actually wear them on duty.
szBRDesc: Very Light vest that still offers the protection of its Heavy counterparts. Don't leave home without one!

szItemDesc: Currently in service throughout the world with Bomb Disposal Teams, the EOD Bomb Disposal Suit is a state-of-the-art garment specifically designed to give the highest level of protection with the maximum comfort and flexibility to the user.
szBRDesc: The EOD helmet is a state-of-the-art garment specifically designed to give the highest level of protection with the maximum comfort and flexibility to the user.

szItemDesc: Currently in service throughout the world with Bomb Disposal Teams, the EOD Bomb Disposal Suit is a state-of-the-art garment specifically designed to give the highest level of protection with the maximum comfort and flexibility to the user.
szBRDesc: Unless you have a higly skilled explosives expert on your team, or have shares in a wheelchair producing company, this piece is a must for every self respecting merc.

szItemDesc: Currently in service throughout the world with Bomb Disposal Teams, the PRO EOD Bomb Disposal Suit is a state-of-the-art garment specifically designed to give the highest level of protection with the maximum comfort and flexibility to the user.
szBRDesc: Unless you have a higly skilled explosives expert on your team, or have shares in a bodybag producing company, this piece is a must for every self respecting merc.

szItemDesc: Either as a companion to the Ghillie suit or on its own, the Ghillie Hood camouflages your most important piece of equipment: your head.
szBRDesc: The finishing touch for your ghillie suit. Also usefull to keep the sun out of your eyes and as mosquito net.

szItemDesc: High Quality Jute Thread is sewn directly on to Military BDU trousers. The sewn on Jute thread covers the back and the front.
szBRDesc: Unless you plan to wear jeans under your Ghillie suit, these pants are a must have if you are going for a covert approach.

szItemDesc: High Quality Jute Thread is sewn directly on to a Military BDU 4 pocket coat. The sewn on Jute thread covers the entire jacket in the front and the back, and has an attached hood.
szBRDesc: Whether you are spying on that cute looking girl next door, or sneaking up to that perfect spot overlooking an enemy base, this vest will make sure nobody sees you.

szItemDesc: The most demanding ballistic requirements can be met by a helmet made from a specially formed Twaron laminate. Its low weight makes it much more comfortable to wear than the traditional steel helmet.
szBRDesc: One of the best helmets money can buy!  Contact us if you want them in blue for that genuine "UN-look".

szItemDesc: These leg protectors are made from high tensile para-aramid fiber.
szBRDesc: Protect your lower half from small arms fire and fragmentation damage with a pair of Twaron trousers.

szItemDesc: Twaron Microfilament in bullet resistant vests makes protective clothing lighter, more flexible, and easier to wear.
szBRDesc: The use of Twaron CT Microfilament in bullet resistant vests makes protective clothing lighter, more flexible, and easier to wear. In short, the most efficient protection system on the market today.

szItemDesc: This Helmet has been treated with Compound-18 for added ballistic protection.
szBRDesc: Catching a bullet high and inside ruins anyone's day. Prevent it with a C-18 treated helmet.

szItemDesc: The tensile strength of these Dyneema leggings has been improved by a treatment with Compound-18.
szBRDesc: Contrary to what you see in the movies, there really is no 'safe place' on the human body to get shot. These treated trousers are worth the investment.

szItemDesc: Permeation with Compound-18 boosts this vest's capacity for resisting trauma from bullets, fragments and other battlefield detritus.
szBRDesc: This treated Dyneema vest prohibits painful penetrating trauma.

szItemDesc: The aramid fibers in this vest have been significantly strengthened by the addition of Compound-18.
szBRDesc: C-18 has vastly improved the protective capacity of this armor.

szBRDesc: Coating with Crepitus goo makes this item the ultimate in protective head gear.

szItemDesc: Complete saturation with crepitus fluid bolsters the defensive capability of these bonded armor leggings.
szBRDesc: Complete saturation with crepitus fluid bolsters the defensive capability of these bonded armor leggings.

szItemDesc: Looking at a pile of alien amniotic fluid, my first thought wouldn't have been "Hey, I wonder if smearing this on my body armor will improve its performance?" There are rewards for creativity and improvisation after all.
szBRDesc: Ballistic inserts, available seperately from Bobby Ray's, would be the perfect addition to this already formidable coated armor.

szBRDesc: Coated leg protectors keep your stock body in mint condition.

szItemDesc: A liberal application of alien goo has strengthened the protective properties of this vest.
szBRDesc: This crepitus coated vest will keep unwanted foreign objects from entering your chest cavity at high speed.

szItemDesc: An alternative to ceramic inserts that is cheaper and lighter, but also a bit less effective.
szBRDesc: Can't afford ceramic inserts for your troops? This cost effective alternative might be of interest to you: the T-15 titanium plate comes in different shapes and sizes to fit any ballistic carrier.

szItemDesc: Not just for unruly kids with skateboards and spray cans, these kneepads will prevent unwanted damage to your, you guessed it, knees.
szBRDesc: Not just for unruly kids with skateboards and spray cans, these kneepads will prevent unwanted damage to your, you guessed it, knees.

szItemDesc: This unique upgrade kit can be used to upgrade any standard kevlar helmet to its stealth ops counterpart.
szBRDesc: Upgrade your helmet today! From standard kevlar helmet to high-tech stealth operations head protection in no time! This kit includes all the necessary tools for such conversion.

szItemDesc: This upgrade kit contains the necessary components and tools to convert a common kevlar vest into the state-of-the-art Stealth Ops vest.
szBRDesc: Need a suit for the next stealth mission? If you already have a standard kevlar vest, all you need is this upgrade kit and a few minutes of your time!

szItemDesc: All you ever need to upgrade your kevlar leggings to those used by stealth operatives.
szBRDesc: Making too much noise while walking around? With this upgrade kit you'll mute your kevlar leggings forever.

szItemDesc: This upgrade kit contains the necessary components and tools to convert a kevlar, guardian or twaron vest into camouflaged recon vest.
szBRDesc: Make a light, camouflaged recon vest today! With this upgrade kit it's easier than ever!

szItemDesc: All you ever need to upgrade your kevlar or twaron leggings to those used by recon operatives.
szBRDesc: Uncomfortable leggings? No camouflage pattern? With this upgrade kit your kevlar or twaron leggings might become first class recon gear!

szItemDesc: This upgrade kit contains the necessary components and tools to convert a kevlar, guardian, twaron, spectra or dyneema vest into medic vest.
szBRDesc: You don't have to worry where to put the first aid kit. With this upgrade kit you'll get enough place for all important medicine you need in your vest.

szItemDesc: All you ever need to upgrade your kevlar, twaron, spectra or dyneema leggings to those used by medic operatives.
szBRDesc: Get this kit before your buddy bleeds to death and upgrade your leggings today! A serious medic wouldn't neglect this one.

szItemDesc: This upgrade kit contains the necessary components and tools to convert a kevlar, guardian, twaron, spectra or dyneema vest into mechanic-demolitions vest.
szBRDesc: Never enough room for your tools? Need an extra pocket for the remote bomb trigger? With this upgrade kit your vest will make a difference.

szItemDesc: All you ever need to upgrade your kevlar, twaron, spectra or dyneema leggings to those used by mechanic and demolitions operatives.
szBRDesc: Ideal upgrade for mechanic and demolitions operatives! More pockets for your tools and demolitions equipment will give you more satisfaction, guaranteed!

szItemDesc: This upgrade kit contains the necessary components and tools to convert a kevlar, guardian, twaron, spectra or dyneema vest into field operative vest.
szBRDesc: Spending too much time outside? Upgrade your vest using this kit and enjoy more comfort and protection than ever!

szItemDesc: All you ever need to upgrade your kevlar, twaron, spectra or dyneema leggings to those used by field operatives.
szBRDesc: No matter if you're a professional merc or a kid spending too much time playing outside - this upgrade kit is all your leggings need.

szItemDesc: This cover will make your helmet less conspicuous.
szBRDesc: Shining brightly helmets are history! One of these camouflaged covers is a perfect upgrade for your helmet.

szItemDesc: This cover will make your helmet less conspicuous. It has additional straps which can be used to mount leaves or other greenery to it, providing better camouflage.
szBRDesc: Let the grass grow on your head! The straps on this helmet are perfect mount points for any material made by Mother nature.

szItemDesc: A sturdy large frame revolver for the .44 Magnum round.
szBRDesc: I hate to say it, but Harry Callahan would've looked cooler carrying an Anaconda instead of a Model 29.

szItemDesc: Another French quality revolver. Its only drawback is the smaller ammo capacity, compared to a .357 Desert Eagle pistol.
szBRDesc: The patented Manurhin MR96 design is a revolution in revolver engineering. The grip - a long-lasting rubber design specific to this revolver - allows continuous firing of the most powerful loads without fatigue.

szItemDesc: Yet another fine service pistol from FN.
szBRDesc: This is the civilian version of the new all-black military FNP-9, with the same qualities, of course.

szItemDesc: Another pistol from FN. A little bit harder to control due to the heavy trigger-pull, but a bit more reliable if ammo of dubious quality is used.
szBRDesc: A new service pistol from FN, this one is a true DAO pistol, which makes it somewhat more reliable, thought the trigger-pull may be a bit much for some people.

szItemDesc: Announced in 2007, this new pistol is FN's latest addition to the civilian and law enforcement market.
szBRDesc: Brand new in the line of FN's new pistols (Forty-Nine, PRO-9), this one is chambered for the good old and never dying .45ACP-round.

szItemDesc: A sturdy .44 Magnum revolver.
szBRDesc: Probably the most famous Magnum revolver, due to its appearance in the Dirty Harry movies.

szItemDesc: Someone was obviously so impressed by the toy that he made a real one. Go Figure...
szBRDesc: Formerly only available as a toy-gun, we can now offer a real version of this stylish gun. Beware of frauds at Ebay, people may try to sell you the toy for real. Only we offer the genuine article.

szItemDesc: Mostly based on S&W revolvers, but with a few features of its own, the MR-73 is the backbone of Manurhin's revolver production.
szBRDesc: A French police revolver in use with GIGN, the French counter-terrorist unit, which tells alot about the quality of this gun.

szItemDesc: A stock with Picatinny rails (so that your M14 or M21 rifle can take advantage of more modern add-ons) and a replacable shoulder stock.
szBRDesc: This is the "Enhanced Battle Rifle" stock. Just drop your M14/M21 system into it, and mount all the modern goodies that do not fit onto the vintage M14.

szItemDesc: This is the M14 barrel and action dropped into a new stock with Picatinny Rails, to take advantage of more modern add-ons.
szBRDesc: Not buyable at BR.

szItemDesc: The M21 tactical rifle is the sniper version of the M14.  An accurate rifle with good stopping power. Somebody dropped this one into the EBR-stock that was originally meant for the M14 rifle.
szBRDesc: Not buyable at BR.

szItemDesc: The short version of the SDASS's predecessor as a combat shotgun.
szBRDesc: An Italian shotgun for police/military use, especially useful in house clearing. It includes Picatinny Rails on the receiver and the pump-action handle.

szItemDesc: A new Italian combat shotgun with rails for adding specialized equipment.
szBRDesc: This is a new Italian shotgun developed for police/military use. It includes Picatinny Rails on the receiver and the pump-action handle.

szItemDesc: A 10mm pistol based on the Colt Commander design, i.e. with a shorter barrel than the Colt Government models.
szBRDesc: Produced from stainless steel and to very tight tolerances, the Kimber Eclipse is a high quality pistol. The Pro II is the intermediate version between the Ultra II and the Custom II, and like the Custom II, it can be equipped with better sights.

szItemDesc: The Commando Mortar is a 60mm caliber mortar, slightly lighter and faster than the M224.
szBRDesc: The Commando Mortar is a 60mm caliber mortar, slightly lighter and faster than the M224.

szItemDesc: The Product Improved version of the M203 fits a lot of rifles, thanks to some ingenious adapters that come with the launcher. Special foregrip available. Cannot shoot grenades of more than standard length.
szBRDesc: Everyone wanted a M203, and now they can. The much improved M203PI does not only work with the M16 and M4, but with several European and some Israeli rifles as well.

szItemDesc: This Russian made pump-action grenade launcher fires 43mm ordnance.
szBRDesc: Compact and light-weight, this launcher can quickly dispense a variety of deadly payloads.

szItemDesc: An underbarrel mounted grenade launcher for Russian made assault rifles. The GP-30 Obuvka fires 40mm VOG-25 and VOG-25P grenades.
szBRDesc: An improved model of the GP-25 Kostyor, the GP-30 Obuvka features a sighting recticle and a recoil buffer to protect the rifle to which it is attached. The GP-30 fires 40mm VOG-25 and VOG-25P grenades.

szItemDesc: The Anbau-Granatwerfer 36 is an underbarrel grenade launcher for most of HK's modern rifles. Does not fit the short G36C, though.
szBRDesc: Need some extra firepower on your G36? This oversized pistol does the trick. Can launch all standard NATO 40mm grenades.

szItemDesc: The Milkor MGL six-shot 40mm grenade launcher is the world's first mass-produced multi-shot, rapid-fire 40mm hand-held weapon.
szBRDesc: The Milkor MGL six-shot 40mm grenade launcher is the world's first mass-produced multi-shot, rapid-fire 40mm hand-held weapon.  The MGL can fire six shots in less than three seconds, making it essential in dealing with ambush situations and in urban warfare.

szItemDesc: Light-weight, retractable 40mm Russian grenade launcher for the grenadier in your squad. The RGM Kastet fires 40mm VOG-25 and VOG-25P grenades.

szItemDesc: Operating like a computer triggered Roman candle, Metal Storm's grenade system is perhaps the lightest and least bulky complete multi-shot launcher around.

szBRDesc: If you need to convert your SCAR-H to the Russian 7.62x39mm caliber, here are the necessary parts: A new CQC-barrel, bolt, and triggergroup with magazine well.

szItemDesc: This kit contains the necessary parts to convert your SCAR-H to the 7.62x39mm caliber long-barreled variant.
szBRDesc: If you need to convert your SCAR-H to the Russian 7.62x39mm caliber, here are the necessary parts: A new SV-barrel, bolt, and triggergroup with magazine well.

szBRDesc: Not for sale through BR

szItemDesc: The leftover parts after you converted your SCAR-H to another caliber. Of course, with these you can change the gun back again.
szBRDesc: Not for sale through BR

szItemDesc: A short barrel to change the SCAR-WP into the CQC version.
szBRDesc: Not for sale through BR.

szItemDesc: A long barrel to change the SCAR-WP into the SV version.
szBRDesc: This long barrel changes your SCAR-WP into the sniper variant.

szItemDesc: .40 S&W emerged in the late 1990s as "middle of the road" round with more stopping power than the 9mm and more penetration than the .45ACP.
szBRDesc: .40 S&W is a popular ammunition among many law enforcement officers.

szItemDesc: This hollow point ammo gives increased punch to the the .40 S&W's already significant stopping power.
szBRDesc: The expansion power of HP adds substance to this powerful pistol ammunition.

szItemDesc: 30 rounds of .40 S&W armor piercing ammo.
szBRDesc: Punch holes in the competition with these handy AP rounds.

szItemDesc: A fruitful marriage of penerating power and game-stopping expansion in .40 caliber.
szBRDesc: Armored targets will go down and stay down when you tag them with this potent AET round.

szItemDesc: If 30 rounds of Glaser Safety ammo fail to make your point, the conversation wasn't worth having to begin with.
szBRDesc: Thirty rounds of frangible fun. All of the man-stopping power, none of the over-penetration.

szItemDesc: 30 rounds of match grade .40 S&W; added range with the same mild recoil.
szBRDesc: Competitive shooting or life and death struggle, match ammo extends your reach.

szItemDesc: The most renowned silent, fast projectile weapon of Ninpo Taijutsu.
szBRDesc: Silent, swift, and effective with razor-sharp edges.

szItemDesc: In the right hands this is one of the most dangerous and compact weapons in martial arts.
szBRDesc: This is one of the favoured weapons of Ninpo Taijutsu.

szItemDesc: This is the pride of the samurai.
szBRDesc: This is a rare Japanese masterpiece, decorated with dragons. It can chop through bamboo like a hot knife through butter!

szItemDesc: This 42-round magazine of 5.56 Remington hollow point ammo is a variation of the civilian .223 hunting round. Like the .223, it is designed to maximize nerve shock and blood loss.
szBRDesc: This is the economical choice for target shooting, hunting, or stopping potential long-range muggings. These 42 rounds of 50 grain .223 JHP can save your life and your pocket book.

szItemDesc: These 42 rounds of NATO standard light full metal jacket ammunition have the ability to tumble within its target to create a much larger wound than what is normally expected from a such small bullet.
szBRDesc: This 42-round magazine is filled with our NATO standard 5.56mm. This round's steel penetrator makes it possible to beat all but the best in today's body armor.

szItemDesc: If 42 rounds of Glaser Safety ammo fail to make your point, the conversation wasn't worth having to begin with.
szBRDesc: Forty-two rounds of frangible fun. All of the man-stopping power, none of the over-penetration.

szItemDesc: Burst fire doesn't have to be a guessing game anymore with 42 rounds of tracer ammo.
szBRDesc: Tracer ammo ensures putting those shots on target when it counts.

szItemDesc: This match grade ammo will add extra range to your 5.56mm assault rifle.
szBRDesc: Close only counts with horseshoes and hand-grenades, for an extra edge load up on match ammunition.

szItemDesc: Added expansion in a quiet 42 round package.
szBRDesc: Extra punch minus the noise with this 5.56mm ammo.

szItemDesc: Pump em' full of holes without waking up the countryside. Cold loaded ammo is 40% quieter than standard full metal jacket rounds.
szBRDesc: This 42-round magazine of ammunition will leave your enemies as cold as the rounds themselves, and is as silent as an Artic wind.

szItemDesc: This kit can be used to store all kinds of medical equipment like boosters, canteen, and first aid kit.
szBRDesc: Handy compact kit for medical equipment. Comes with a regeneration booster.

szItemDesc: Even more compact than the P228, this gun is easily concealed.
szBRDesc: Want something more compact than a P228? The P239 SAS makes for easy concealed carrying with SIG's reduced snag design.

szItemDesc: A new version of the AUG, this one is chambered for the 6.8mm SPC caliber and comes with Picatinny rails.
szBRDesc: This latest version of the famous Steyr AUG has rails instead of a fixed optical sight and foregrip. Chambered in the new 6.8x43mm SPC caliber.

szItemDesc: A shorter version of the standard HK 416.
szBRDesc: This is just a HK 416 with a shorter barrel, for those who often do CQB.

szItemDesc: Long in use with the Italian Police, this is an easy to use SMG.
szBRDesc: The built-in foregrip on this older Beretta SMG lets you handle the gun easily even if the folding stock has not been deployed.

szItemDesc: A panel with four individual pockets to store up to four 40mm grenades.
szBRDesc: Four pockets mounted on a panel that can be clipped to your load bearing equipment. The long adjustable straps let you store 40mm grenades on any length.

szItemDesc: A sniperized version of the Galil assault rifle. More like a DMR than a real sniper rifle.
szBRDesc: This was a standard Galil, until someone decided to make a sniper rifle from it.

szItemDesc: This has a barrel that is slightly longer than on the standard HK 416.
szBRDesc: If you want more range than a standard 416 has, take this one.

szItemDesc: A rather simple and full auto-only SMG.
szBRDesc: Adopted by the Australian army who considered it to be more reliable than the Thompson SMG. Top-feeding magazine precludes alternative sights, though.

szItemDesc: The DMR variant of the HK 416.
szBRDesc: A Designated Marksman Rifle based on the Heckler & Koch 416.

szItemDesc: This is Heckler & Koch's competitor to FN's FiveseveN.
szBRDesc: The companion pistol to the HK MP7 PDW. These are pre-production models that may deviate from serial production.

szItemDesc: Actually a M1 Carbine in a new dress.
szBRDesc: A very new weapon for an old caliber, the HEZI is quite effective for its odd shape.

szItemDesc: When the Germans build up the Bundeswehr they took the MG42, renamed it MG3, and took down the firing rate somewhat. Because, it was still the best GPMG of the world at that time. In use in several other countries as well.
szBRDesc: Despite various nicknames, this is a dead serious gun. With attachment points for both a bipod or a tripod, an Anti-Air sight, and very easily replaced barrels, you can see why this is THE General Purpose Machine Gun.

szItemDesc: The LMG version of the M4 assault rifle.
szBRDesc: Ares changed the M4 assault rifle to a LMG with a completely new upper receiver. Comes with a foregrip for better control during fullauto.

szItemDesc: The 7.62x51mm version of the HK 416.
szBRDesc: This is the 7.62x51mm version of Heckler & Koch's new HK 416.

szItemDesc: The action of Beretta's Storm pistol inside a rifle stock.
szBRDesc: A futuristic looking rifle firing an unsurpassed pistol round, the .45ACP. This version has a magazine well that accepts hi-cap magazines.

szItemDesc: A vest designed for carrying quite some of the most important consumables on a battlefield: ammo.
szBRDesc: The Tactical Tailor Assault Vest is for primary combat soldiers, and can carry 12 AR magazines, or whatever you need.

szItemDesc: A panel with four individual pockets to store up to four 40mm grenades.
szBRDesc: A quadruple pouch mounted on a leg rig. The long adjustable straps let you store 40mm grenades on any length.

szItemDesc: A double pouch that can carry two long non-standard mags.
szBRDesc: A pouch for carrying two longer magazines (like P90-mags) strapped to the upper thigh.

szItemDesc: A large pouch that can carry an ammo box.
szBRDesc: This pouch is designed to hold the ammo box for your machinegun. Mounted onto a leg rig.

szItemDesc: A vest that is designed to carry magazines mostly.
szBRDesc: A tactical vest that can carry an assortment of AR and pistol magazines.

szItemDesc: A versatile vest with pockets of different sizes, 8 of them designed especially for 40mm grenades.
szBRDesc: Your dedicated grenadier will love this vest, with its eight 40mm grenade pockets. Although it's a police vest, you need not necessarily load only tear gas...

szItemDesc: A German assault vest.
szBRDesc: A German assault vest. What you can't see on the picture is the large pocket at the left side, near the back of the vest.

szItemDesc: A very versatile vest.
szBRDesc: The high number of pockets of various sizes lets you carry a lot of different things. Russian ingenuity at its best.

szItemDesc: A vest with mostly AK magazine pockets.
szBRDesc: This is a vest for the primary combat soldier, who needs lots of assault rifle magazines.

szItemDesc: A versatile Russian special forces vest.
szBRDesc: Designed for carrying magazines, grenades, and a few other things, this is the Russian special forces vest.

szItemDesc: A vest with two larger pockets for carrying some big things.
szBRDesc: The Tactical Tailor Utility Vest is for those who are not primary combat soldiers, but have other duties as well.

szItemDesc: Several pouches mounted onto a harness.
szBRDesc: Load Bearing Equipment lets you carry your equipment into battle.

szItemDesc: A tactical holster that rides on the upper thigh, it has a pocket for a spare magazine.
szBRDesc: The Eagle SAS Tactical Holster carries a medium pistol and a spare magazine.

szItemDesc: A leg rig outfitted with a medium pistol holster and a triple pistol mag pouch.
szBRDesc: This Tactical Tailor Leg Rig can carry a pistol and three magazines.

szItemDesc: A leg rig for large pistols or small machinepistols. Can carry two additional magazines.
szBRDesc: With this Holster you can strap a small machinepistol or large pistol to your upper thigh. Has a pocket for two additional magazines.

szItemDesc: The backpack part of the TIMS set. You can mount the combat pack onto it in place of the flap.
szBRDesc: If you want to carry all sorts of big things cross-country, you'll need a backpack like this one. Can be worn in conjunction with a TIMS combat pack.

szItemDesc: A backpack with two outer pockets.
szBRDesc: For a little bit of more organization, the ARUC backpack has two outer pockets for those items you need fast at hand.

szItemDesc: A backpack with lots of outer pockets.
szBRDesc: You do not want to rummage through the main compartment of your backpack for that elusive piece of gear that always sits at the bottom? This one has lots of outer pockets, to store your items for easy access.

szItemDesc: This is the combat pack partner to the TIMS backpack.
szBRDesc: This combat pack can be worn in conjunction with the TIMS backpack, so you may want to have a look at the backpack as well.

szItemDesc: A combat pack with an extra pocket on the outside.
szBRDesc: You want storage capacity to lug some things around during combat, but a backpack slows you down to much. This smaller combat pack may be the solution to your needs.

szItemDesc: A multi-pocket combat pack.
szBRDesc: If you need to carry a very diverse assortment of goodies into combat, this is the combat pack for you!

szItemDesc: A combination of a double AR-Mag pouch with three grenade pouches.
szBRDesc: This leg rig mounts a double AR-magazine pouch and three individual grenade pouches. Great for your primary combat soldiers.

szItemDesc: A combination of a double AR-Mag pouch and a utility pouch.
szBRDesc: A double AR-magazine pouch and a larger utility pouch mounted together on a leg rig, this is useful for carrying larger things like explosives.

szItemDesc: Here a utility pouch was combined with a canteen pouch.
szBRDesc: This leg rig has a utility pouch mounted besides a canteen pouch.

szItemDesc: A combination of a utility pouch with three grenade pouches.
szBRDesc: Here we have a utility pouch combined with three individual grenade pouches.

szItemDesc: This combo has a utility pouch with two pouches for oddly shaped magazines.
szBRDesc: This leg rig offers a utility pouch together with two large mag pouches for those extremely long P90 or G11 magazines (or similar odd magazines).

szItemDesc: A combination of two large magazine pouches with two grenade pouches.
szBRDesc: This leg rig mounts two large magazine pouches combined with two individual grenade pouches.

szItemDesc: A vest as it is often used by hunters and photographers.
szBRDesc: Not for sale through BR.

szItemDesc: An ugly SMG developed with reliability as its main focus (besides spitting lead).
szBRDesc: This Italian SMG is very reliable due to some very interesting design features, like forcing air around the barrel with every shot to keep it cool.

szItemDesc: An older French SMG that can be folded down to a small package.
szBRDesc: This is a fullauto-only French Army SMG, unlike the police versions that have semiauto, too. The magazine well can be folded along the barrel for easy storage and acts as a foregrip.

szItemDesc: This old Swiss SMG is fullauto-only and quite heavy, but its range is up to par with modern SMGs.
szBRDesc: This old Swiss SMG is fullauto-only and quite heavy, but its range is up to par with modern SMGs. It was developed in the 1930s by Adolf Furrer, manager of SIG Armory at Bern, Switzerland.

szItemDesc: German scope for the Gewehr 98 and the Karabiner 98k. The Scope sits off-center on the side mount, so you can access the iron sights in case of emergencies.
szBRDesc: This vintage scope will fit the German Mauser WW-II rifles.

szItemDesc: British scope used during WW-II.
szBRDesc: A WW-II era scope of British manufacture, this was also used by other allied forces during that war.

szItemDesc: Russian WW-II era scope. It sits off-center on the side mount, so you can access the iron sights in case of emergencies.
szBRDesc: Simply THE scope to mount onto the Mosin-Nagant rifle.

szItemDesc: These match sights have been made for precision during competition shooting.
szBRDesc: Fully adjustable iron sights to go with a Colt 1911, Glock, HK USP, or SIG pistol.

szItemDesc: This shirt is designed to go under a ballistic vest, therefore DPM is only on the visible parts.
szBRDesc: There's no need to have a fully camoed shirt when you wear a ballistic vest over it anyway, so this shirt was designed for use with those vests.

szItemDesc: A set of forward Picatinny Rails and a rail to replace the carrying grip
szBRDesc: Change your G36/G36K/MG36 to a more versatile gun with this set of Picatinny Rails.

szItemDesc: A carrying grip with integrated optics and a standard handguard.
szBRDesc: The G36 standard equipment: Handguard and Carry Grip with mounted dual optics.

szItemDesc: Not as bulky or heavy as other LMG's, this gun still has a rate of fire that will frappe an enemy in no time.
szBRDesc: HK has blessed us with their new versatile, multi-role squad machine gun. This version has the Bundeswehr grip with integrated optics.

szItemDesc: Designed by the Compania de Estudios Tecnicos de Materiales Especiales, the Ameli looks as if it was derived from the MG42, but its mechanism is quite different.
szBRDesc: The Ameli we have in stock are the 'light-bolt'-versions with a higher rate of fire than the 'heavy-bolt'-model. Comes with bipod.

szItemDesc: A flare normally used for emergency purposes.
szBRDesc: Brighter than chemical lightsticks, but also comparatively short-lived, these flares can light up the night for you.

szItemDesc: Almost as light as some heavier pistols, this is the ideal sidearm for the modern Private Military Contractor.
szBRDesc: A new PDW on the market, this little beauty was made by the Knight Armament Corporation and fires the new 6x35mm round.

szItemDesc: Yet another new 6x35mm PDW, and a very effective one.
szBRDesc: Just out of prototype stage, this new PDW is chambered for 6x35mm ammo. The SciFi-look belittles its effectiveness, though.

szItemDesc: This Automag is chambered for the .50 AE caliber.
szBRDesc: The .50 Action Express version of Galena's line of Automag pistols.

szItemDesc: Intended to replace the pistol as the sidearm, this gun was more often used as a light rifle during WW-II.
szBRDesc: The good old M1 Carbine, still on the market for WW-II enthusiasts and gun collectors.

szItemDesc: A very sturdy revolver, the Python has a reputation for accuracy.
szBRDesc: The first 'modern' revolver after WW-II, it was made in several versions.

szItemDesc: Despite having stopping power in a small package, this was a not so popular gun, due to high maintenace requirements and low controllability in fullauto fire.
szBRDesc: An even shorter version of the G3KA4 battle rifle, this was made in Great Britain for the SAS.

szItemDesc: This vest has a machine pistol holster incorporated.
szBRDesc: The Tactical Tailor 1F Vest is useful if your legs already carry some rigs, but you still want to pack a large sidearm. The holster near the back of the vest will fit most machine pistols.

szItemDesc: Either as a companion to the Ghillie suit or on its own, the Ghillie Hood camouflages your most important piece of equipment: your head.
szBRDesc: The finishing touch for your ghillie suit. Also usefull to keep the sun out of your eyes and as mosquito net.

szItemDesc: High Quality Jute Thread is sewn directly on to Military BDU trousers. The sewn on Jute thread covers the back and the front.
szBRDesc: Unless you plan to wear jeans under your Ghillie suit, these pants are a must have if you are going for a covert approach.

szItemDesc: High Quality Jute Thread is sewn directly on to a Military BDU 4 pocket coat. The sewn on Jute thread covers the entire jacket in the front and the back, and has an attached hood.
szBRDesc: Whether you are spying on that cute looking girl next door, or sneaking up to that perfect spot overlooking an enemy base, this vest will make sure nobody sees you.

szItemDesc: A clip-on holster for small revolvers, with two separate speedloader pockets.
szBRDesc: This holster can be clipped onto your equipment and fits small revolvers. Comes with two separate speedloader pockets that are also of the clip-on type.

szItemDesc: What a Rail Kit and a bit of black paint can do to your SL8! Now you can mount a few goodies that would not fit on a standard one.
szBRDesc: What a Rail Kit and a bit of black paint can do to your SL8! Now you can mount a few goodies that would not fit on a standard one.

szItemDesc: A durable tool for fixing pipes and obnoxious people.
szBRDesc: Not for sale at BR.

szItemDesc: This vest can take 2 ammo belts for your machinegun, or several drums.
szBRDesc: Your machinegunner will love this vest, provided he's strong enough to wear it when it is filled to capacity.

szItemDesc: This leg rig has a first aid pouch with several small belt loops for the neat storage of syringes.
